The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 29 September is 382,686 (679.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 September, there were 33,159 new confirmed cases (58.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 September, there were 21,678 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 53% (11481 extra cases).
